# Cloudflare Pages header rules.
#
# The service worker MUST NOT be held in the browser's HTTP cache, or a device can keep
# revalidating against a stale copy and never discover a new version — which is exactly
# how installs got pinned to a broken worker on iOS. no-cache = store but always
# revalidate (via ETag), so every visit picks up a new worker immediately.
/service-worker.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache

# Same reasoning for the manifest: it gates which episodes/quizzes appear, so it should
# always be revalidated rather than served stale from the HTTP cache.
/manifest.json
  Cache-Control: no-cache
